The error is caused by the `{% endwith %}` tag, which is not a built-in Django template tag. The `with` tag is used to create a new context for variable values, and it needs to be closed with the `{% endwith %}` tag. However, Django doesn't recognize this tag by default.

To fix this error, you need to load the `with` template tag library in your template. Add the following line at the top of your template file:

```html
{% load static %}
{% load with %}  {# Load the 'with' template tag library #}

{% extends 'base.html' %}

{% block content %}
...
```

After adding this line, Django will recognize the `{% with %}` and `{% endwith %}` tags, and the error should be resolved.

Alternatively, if you don't want to use the `with` tag, you can refactor the code to use regular Django template syntax without the `with` tag. Here's an example:

```html
{% extends 'base.html' %}

{% block content %}
<h2>Wszystkie typy</h2>

<div class="user-predictions">
    {% for data in user_data %}
    <div class="card">
        <h3>{{ data.user.username }}</h3>

        <h4>Mecze:</h4>
        <table class="prediction-table">
            <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Gospodarze</th>
                <th>Gole gospodarzy</th>
                <th>Gole goci</th>
                <th>Gocie</th>
                <th>Wynik</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            {% for bet in data.bets %}
            {% if bet.match.actualresults %}
            {% with actual=bet.match.actualresults %}
            {% with is_exact_score=actual.home_team_score == bet.home_team_score and actual.away_team_score == bet.away_team_score %}
            {% with is_correct_result=(actual.home_team_score > actual.away_team_score and bet.home_team_score > bet.away_team_score) or
                                       (actual.home_team_score < actual.away_team_score and bet.home_team_score < bet.away_team_score) or
                                       (actual.home_team_score == actual.away_team_score and bet.home_team_score == bet.away_team_score) %}
            <tr>
                <td>{{ bet.match.home_team }}</td>
                <td>{{ bet.home_team_score }}</td>
                <td>{{ bet.away_team_score }}</td>
                <td>{{ bet.match.away_team }}</td>
                <td class="{% if is_exact_score %}
                            exact-score
                            {% elif is_correct_result %}
                            correct-result
                            {% else %}
                            wrong-result
                            {% endif %}">
                    {% if is_exact_score %}
                    <span>Trafiony dokadny wynik</span>
                    {% elif is_correct_result %}
                    Trafiony rezultat
                    {% else %}
                    Nietrafiony
                    {% endif %}
                </td>
            </tr>
            {% endwith %}
            {% endwith %}
            {% endwith %}
            {% else %}
            <tr>
                <td>{{ bet.match.home_team }}</td>
                <td>{{ bet.home_team_score }}</td>
                <td>{{ bet.away_team_score }}</td>
                <td>{{ bet.match.away_team }}</td>
                <td class="wrong-result">No Result</td>
            </tr>
            {% endif %}
            {% endfor %}
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>Czarny ko:
            {% if data.underdog %}
            <span class="{% if data.underdog.team == selected_winner %}exact{% else %}wrong-result{% endif %}"><strong>{{ data.underdog.team }}</strong></span>
            {% else %}
            <span><strong>Brak wyboru</strong></span>
        </p>
        {% endif %}

        <p>Krl strzelcw:
            {% if data.top_scorer %}
            <span class="{% if data.top_scorer.player == selected_top_scorer %}exact{% else %}wrong-result{% endif %}"><strong>{{ data.top_scorer.player }}</strong></span>
            {% else %}
            <span><strong>Brak wyboru</strong></span>
        </p>
        {% endif %}

        <p>Zwycizca turnieju:
            {% if data.tournament_winner %}
            <span class="{% if data.tournament_winner.team == selected_winner %}exact{% else %}wrong-result{% endif %}"><strong>{{ data.tournament_winner.team }}</strong></span>
            {% else %}
            <span><strong>Brak wyboru</strong></span>
        </p>
        {% endif %}
    </div>
    <hr>
    {% endfor %}
</div>
{% endblock %}
```

In this version, the `with` tag is used multiple times to create separate contexts for the variables `actual`, `is_exact_score`, and `is_correct_result`. This approach doesn't require loading the `with` template tag library, but it can make the code a bit more verbose and harder to read.

Choose the approach that works best for your project and your team's preferences.

